  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nExclusive to:\nMelonsicle\nFood Info\n12.5\n3\n20\nVeggie\nObject Info\nPerk\nLowers temperature by 10 degrees over 10 seconds.\n3 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x1 x1\n10 secs\n10\nMiscellaneous\n\"watermelonicle\"\n“Cryogenic watermelon.”\n–Wilson\n“Why would you freeze a fruit when you could burn it?”\n–Willow\n“Ha! Melon on a stick.”\n–Wolfgang\n“The melon is in stasis.”\n–Wendy\n“WATERMELON ON ICE”\n–WX-78\n“The melon is entirely encased in an ice lattice.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Wood AND food?!”\n–Woodie\n“The case is cold on the melon.”\n–Maxwell\n“Has an endothermic effect on internal temperatures.”\n–Wagstaff\n“Yöu cannöt fööl me by hiding in frözen fruit, stick.”\n–Wigfrid\n“Just the thing for a hot summer day.”\n–Webber\n“Eat it before it melts!”\n–Walani\n“I feel like a kid again!”\n–Warly\n“A cool treat from me favorite fruit!”\n–Woodlegs\n“WILBA MAKETH SURE TONGUE DOST NAUGHT STICK”\n–Wilba\n“Keeping cool, stick?”\n–Wormwood\n“Frozen fruit on a stick. A meal fit for kings.”\n–Wheeler\n“A good treat for work breaks.”\n–Winona\n“Looks stomachable.”\n–Wortox\n“Chilly melon!”\n–Wurt\n“Further proof that all food is better on a stick!”\n–Walter\n“It tastes like a frozen summer day.”\n–Wanda\nThe Melonsicle is a Fruit Food item introduced in the Reign of Giants DLC. It is inexplicably cooked in the Crock Pot by combining 1 Raw Watermelon, 1 Ice, and 1 Twig.\nNo Meats, Vegetables, or Eggs should be added.\nMelonsicles restore 20 when consumed. This, paired with the fact that the ingredients can be kept fresh forever (Melons left unharvested and Ice stored in Ice Boxes), makes it one of the best Sanity restoring Food items in the game.\nIn addition, Melonsicles decrease the player's perceived temperature by 1 degree per second for 10 seconds when consumed.\nDownloadable Content[edit | edit source]\nMelonsicles are also included in the Shipwrecked DLC, as Watermelons are available through Farming and Ice can be obtained by using an Ice Maker 3000 or by Refining Hail. They can be used to deal with Overheating during the Dry Season.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:\nExcludes:\nExcludes:\nExcludes:\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×2\nUsage[edit | edit source]\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nDespite being covered in Ice, Melonsicles will continue to spoil inside Ice Boxes.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nIcon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
